- An average T cells (CD4+) proportion of 10% or higher might be considered significant in certain medical or biological research contexts; 
- 'At least five samples' implies that the researchers must have contributed multiple samples to be considered in the results.

sql:
SELECT sample_id
FROM samples
WHERE collection_date = (
    SELECT MAX(collection_date)
    FROM samples
);

SELECT researcher_name
FROM researchers
WHERE researcher_id IN (
  SELECT DISTINCT researcher_id
  FROM samples
);

